@deps ds, facade, eventMeta

# Invariants & contracts
  @invariant  project-wide singleton; reads REAPER items + cm directly, owns no take state of its own  @ 4
  @invariant  trackIdx is a visible-column index, not a REAPER slot (see docs/arrangeManager.md)  @ 5
  @invariant  slot palette in ds at track scope under key 'arrangeSlots'; writes via ds:assignAt  @ 6
  @invariant  slot indices 0..61, base62-keyed (util.toBase62); lowest-free, gaps allowed  @ 7
  @invariant  a slot survives while its id is live on the track or parked; reads via ensureSlots  @ 8
  @invariant  deleteTake parks a slot's last instance; deleteSlot alone forever-deletes  @ 9
  @invariant  createAndDropMidi + mintParkedTake mint slots; everything else reuses an existing one  @ 10
  @invariant  takeId is the source-identity chokepoint; takes with no derivable id are skipped  @ 11
  @invariant  reswingAll is sequenceManager folded in; bind loop lives behind the 'tracker' facade  @ 12
  @invariant  natural length in ds 'arrangeNaturalLenQN', nil → util.OPEN; see docs § Natural length  @ 13
  @invariant  a stored natural ≥ source demotes to util.OPEN; see docs § Natural length  @ 14
  @invariant  'arrangeColours' (project scope) maps takeId → colourIdx project-wide  @ 15
  @invariant  arrangeColours allocates lowest-free across live takeIds; ensureColours prunes dead ids  @ 16
  @invariant  placement stamps painter.hueNative(idx) on new takes iff I_CUSTOMCOLOR == 0  @ 17
  @invariant  painter.hue and painter.hueNative share one hash; freshly-stamped takes match the grid  @ 18
  @invariant  render reads serve one cached build; rebuilt on invalidate() or state-count change  @ 19

